{"sequence":24,"timestamp":"2026-05-01T04:44:56.831719719Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-0aa0a026","body":"`src/cli/pr.rs:54-59` resolves and preflights `br` before dispatching every `pr` subcommand, but `src/cli/pr.rs:93-104` shows `pr watch` ignores the resolved path and only calls the GitHub-backed watcher. This makes `ralph-burning pr watch <n>` abort with `BrUnavailable` when `br` is absent even though that path does not invoke `br`, contrary to the scoped requirement to preflight only subcommands that need it. Move the preflight into the `Open` arm, or otherwise gate it to br-using PR subcommands, and add a regression for `pr watch` with `br` absent from PATH.","classification":"fix_current_bead","dedup_key":"5e958725f63bd6da7b69aee8f6ebac240958047d53ed16398a46d84b755ece7b","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.5-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260501034351","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
